description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1675, 1499, 1728

Multiple locations increment from_radio_id:
  from_radio_id = adapter->from_radio_id + 1U;
  ...
  adapter->from_radio_id = from_radio_id;

When from_radio_id reaches UINT32_MAX, it wraps to 0. If Meshtastic clients or this implementation use 0 as a special/invalid ID value, this could cause unexpected behavior.

The Meshtastic protocol documentation should be consulted to determine if ID 0 has special meaning. If so, the increment should skip 0:
  from_radio_id = (adapter->from_radio_id + 1U) ?: 1U;

Note: This is low priority as UINT32_MAX messages would take a very long time to reach.
